Sasarin shot a jet of flame, igniting a small patch of forest, then circled above it, watching for the right moment. Strangely, when he slowed down, the eerie screeching behind him also stopped. Sasarin forgot he had a passenger on his back.
"Come on, Tynuk, you've transformed into a Slakian before!"
"Being able to fly on your own and suddenly being dragged away by a huge pink dragon are two completely different things!"
"Still okay, Cayle?"
Kael clearly disagreed with Nisi's statement. He looked paler than usual, his claws deeply embedded in Sasalin's back, drawing blood from the Slak'ar, yet Sasalin didn't seem to care at all. Nevertheless, Sasalin realized he had frightened his new friend and landed on an empty patch of ground.
"Sorry, sorry, I smell something. I need to take care of it!"
"Did you really have to drag us along too?" Tenuk climbed down from Sasilin's back, sliding to the ground along the tail, and asked sharply. "We left Retwick behind! We abandoned that strong and aggressive giant! How could he possibly find us?"
“He’ll figure it out somehow…” Nisi nodded in agreement. “Rettwick is slow to react, but not stupid.”
"Can Lietwiek drive a car?"
Nisi blinked and turned to look at Tenuk. "Of course he can drive."
"Have you ever seen Retwick drive a car? He doesn't have a truck like yours, and I've never seen him drive a cute little car like Cayler's. He started taking the bus to work purely because you always drove us to work. He only has a bicycle."
A burst of laughter interrupted them. Sassalin suddenly burst into uncontrollable laughter, but no one knew what he was laughing at. It took Sassalin a while to calm down.
"Sorry, sorry, I just imagined it for a moment—your big, armored friend riding a small bicycle designed specifically for Temsen children. The image was so comical! I really wish I had telepathy. This idea is so funny! I must treasure it well!"
Kayer also smiled, because he could imagine what Sasilin was thinking. "Well, well. But what exactly did you smell? Why did you fly so fast?"
Sassarin snorted, took off quickly, and soon disappeared, then flew back and left a corpse in Nisi's presence. It was an Orotharack, a very rare golden-white dragon-like creature. But its head was missing. "Another one is dead. I heard their cries. I smelled their blood. I must protect them, hunt down the killer. This is the will of Isini. Those creatures are nearby."
The powerful Slark suddenly froze. Nisi and Kayer also froze, their attention drawn to a gap at the edge of the clearing. Something huge and black was staring at them, hissing. It suddenly flared open two pairs of massive wings and darted forward, heading straight for Sasarin, completely ignoring the three small figures standing between it and Sasarin. Kayer and Tenuk barely managed to dodge aside, but Nisi found herself dragged to the ground, almost flung onto Sasarin.
Sasarin grabbed Nisi with one hand, using its long and dexterous tail to hurl her over its back, and then leaped into the air. The black creature with two pairs of wings quickly closed in behind.
Kayer snorted, drew out a rifle from behind him, and then opened the bag to take out a belt of ammunition. He fastened the belt around his chest for easy access, but soon realized that Nisi, Sasalin, and the monster had all vanished without a trace.
"Hey, Tenuk, can you transform into a flying animal?" Kayel asked.
"Do you want to chase after him?"
"Trash talk." or "Nonsense."
"But... one of them is a giant monster!"
"What's the big deal? This rifle in my hands has strong firepower and can fire anytime. I just need to see it, and I can bring it down."
Tenuk hesitated for a moment, then took a step back to create some space. With a low, pained groan, his body stretched out, his fur turning into scales, his arms transforming into wings. He quickly became an ordinary light blue Slak, though his eyes remained red.
"Come on up."
Tenuk now looks like an ordinary Slak with neatly arranged scales on his back and a pair of spines that make it easier for Kael to grab. It took Tenuk a long time to take off, but once airborne, it quickly adjusted its direction and made a desperate effort to catch up.
However, Tenuk and Kayel soon realized they were not facing only one opponent. A second dark monster burst up from below them, and Tenuk barely dodged the impact.
"I guess that's another terrifying big monster that Lanelles was worried about," Cayler frowned, trying to shoot the second monster but missing, and quickly reloaded.
Tenuk didn't respond; he was too busy flying toward Nisi and Sasarin, even though another monster was chasing them. Cael turned awkwardly, facing the monster. The monster was chasing them, and Cael thought it was a good sign because it made aiming and shooting easier. Two bullets pierced the monster's upper wing, and it howled in pain before disappearing into the woods. Cael wasn't sure if it was still following them, but he thought it was definitely too slow to catch up.
In front, Sasilin was wildly flailing her body, spitting fire at the black monster. Nisi desperately held onto Sasilin to prevent her from falling. Although the monster was clearly injured, it seemed enraged and unwilling to retreat, and the fireballs had not caused much damage. After Sasilin steadied herself, Nisi seized the opportunity to pull out her trusted shotgun. Of course, a shotgun wouldn't be effective against such a monster, but the scattering bullets might at least scare off this black beast?
